OL,3,CWatchdog reverses ruling that Calvin
OL,4,CKlein poster 'objectified' FKA twigs
OL,6,F"After careful thought, our council,
OL,7,Fthe independent jury that decides
OL,8,Fwhether UK ads break the rules,
OL,9,Fconsiders that the image was not
OL,10,Fsexually explicit, that the ad
OL,11,Fpresented FKA twigs as confident and
OL,12,Fin control and, therefore, that she
OL,13,Fhad not been objectified."
OL,15,FIt added that the council had,
OL,16,Fhowever, maintained its decision that
OL,17,Fthe image was overtly sexual and was
OL,18,Ftherefore not suitable for display in
OL,19,Fan untargeted medium, meaning that ban
OL,20,Fremained in place on that point.
